caption: 18. Child Sexual Abuse and/or Sexual Assault Response Policy and Reporting Procedure
created: 20260405120000000
modified: 20260405120000000
title: Policy4153(s18)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The Board has adopted a uniform child sexual abuse and/or sexual assault response policy and reporting procedure in connection with the implementation of the sexual assault and abuse prevention and awareness program identified or developed by DCF, as outlined in Board Policy 4153 and 4253, ''Child Sexual Abuse and/or Sexual Assault Response Policy and Reporting Procedure''. Upon receipt of any report of child sexual abuse and/or sexual assault from any source, a school employee shall report such suspicion to the Safe School Climate Coordinator in addition to complying with the school employee's obligations under this Policy and the law regarding mandatory reporting of abuse, neglect and sexual assault.

Beginning July 1, 2023, and annually thereafter, information regarding the sexual abuse and assault awareness and prevention program identified or developed by DCF shall be distributed electronically to all school employees, Board members, and the parents or guardians of enrolled students.
